\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql\rtlch\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe2052\hich\fs24\lang2057\loch\fs24\lang2057{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0{ The plugin reads the shooting time of each photo and looks for the reference point with the same time or the two points whose date-time contain it; in this last case the plugin calculates a proportion between times and positions to locate the photo on the 
right distance in the segment between the two points.\line Often the clock of the digital camera isn't synchronized with GPS time; to correct the }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 consequent {error you need to insert the delay of the photos over the reference points. If this value is unknown you
 can select a photo taken in a known place, show its position on the map and change the delay value until the right position is reached.}}
